HEADWORD: Grandee
<hw>Gran*dee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>grande</ets>. See <er>Grand</er>.]</ety> <def>A man of elevated
rank or station; a nobleman. In Spain, a nobleman of the first rank, who
may be covered in the king's presence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

